table.body:
You don't need to do anything to defer your State Pension - as long as you're not claiming any benefits.

If you're claiming benefits you'll need to tell [The Pension Service](http://www.direct.gov.uk/en/Pensionsandretirementplanning/StatePension/DG_180132 "Pension Service"){:rel="external"} you want to defer.

If you're already getting your State Pension, but want to stop claiming it, you should [contact your pension centre.](http://pensions-service.direct.gov.uk/en/find-pension-centre/home.asp "contact your pension centre"){:rel="external"}
